### 1. String Kya Hota Hai?
String = text ya characters ka sequence (jaise "Harsh", 'JavaScript', "123" bhi string hi hai).

JavaScript mein string 3 tareeke se likh sakte ho:

```js
let single = 'Single quotes';
let double = "Double quotes";
let backtick = `Backticks (template literal)`;
```

Sab teeno same hi kaam karte hain, lekin **backticks** (`) sabse powerful hain (baad mein samjhaunga).

### 2. String Creation & Basic Cheezein

```js
let name = "Harsh";
let greeting = 'Hello';
let empty = "";     // empty string
let numberAsString = "42";   // yeh string hai, number nahi
```

### 3. Common String Properties & Methods (Yeh sabse zyada use honge)

| Method/Property | Kaam Kya Karta Hai?                          | Example                              | Output / Result          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|--------------------------|
| length          | String ki length (kitne characters)          | "Harsh".length                       | 5                        |
| toUpperCase()   | Sab capital letters mein                     | "hello".toUpperCase()                | "HELLO"                  |
| toLowerCase()   | Sab small letters mein                       | "HELLO".toLowerCase()                | "hello"                  |
| trim()          | Extra spaces shuru/akhir se hata deta hai    | "  Harsh  ".trim()                   | "Harsh"                  |
| includes()      | Check karta hai word/string hai ya nahi      | "Hello World".includes("World")      | true                     |
| startsWith()    | Shuru se match karta hai                     | "JS is fun".startsWith("JS")         | true                     |
| endsWith()      | End se match karta hai                       | "file.pdf".endsWith(".pdf")          | true                     |
| indexOf()       | Position batata hai (pehla match)            | "hello".indexOf("l")                 | 2 (0-based index)        |
| slice(start, end) | Part nikaalta hai (end optional)           | "Harsh Raj".slice(0, 5)              | "Harsh"                  |
| substring(start, end) | Slice jaisa, negative nahi leta         | "Hello".substring(1, 4)              | "ell"                    |
| split(separator) | String ko array mein tod deta hai            | "a,b,c".split(",")                   | ["a", "b", "c"]          |
| replace(old, new) | Pehla match replace karta hai               | "I like JS".replace("like", "love")  | "I love JS"              |
| replaceAll(old, new) | Sab matches replace (ES2021+)             | "ha ha ha".replaceAll("ha", "ho")    | "ho ho ho"               |

**Practice Examples (file bana `strings.js` mein try kar):**

```js
let fullName = "  Harsh Raj  ";
console.log(fullName.length);          // 11 (spaces count hote hain)
console.log(fullName.trim().length);   // 9

let email = "harsh@example.com";
console.log(email.includes("@"));      // true
console.log(email.startsWith("harsh")); // true
console.log(email.endsWith(".com"));   // true

let greeting = "Hello World";
console.log(greeting.slice(0, 5));     // "Hello"
console.log(greeting.toUpperCase());   // "HELLO WORLD"
```

### 4. String Concatenation (Jodna) – Purana Tareeka

```js
let first = "Hello";
let second = "World";

let message = first + " " + second + "!";   // "Hello World!"
console.log(message);

let age = 20;
let info = "My age is " + age + " years.";   // "My age is 20 years."
```

Problem: Agar bahut saare variables honge toh code ugly ho jaata hai.

### 5. Template Literals (Backticks ``) – Modern & Best Way (ES6+)

Yeh sabse powerful hai. Backticks (`) use karo aur **${variable}** se value daalo.

```js
let user = "Harsh";
let age = 20;
let city = "Lucknow";

let intro = `Hello, mera naam ${user} hai. 
Meri umar ${age} saal hai aur main ${city} se hoon.`;

console.log(intro);
// Output:
// Hello, mera naam Harsh hai. 
// Meri umar 20 saal hai aur main Lucknow se hoon.
```

**Fayde:**
- Multi-line strings asaan (enter daba sakte ho)
- Variables directly daal sakte ho ${}
- Expressions bhi chalte hain: `${2 + 3}` → 5
- Code clean aur padhne mein easy

**Aur Example:**

```js
let price = 500;
let qty = 3;
let total = `Total bill: ₹${price * qty}`;   // "Total bill: ₹1500"
console.log(total);

let isAdult = age >= 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor";
let status = `User status: ${isAdult}`;
```

### Quick Summary Table (Yaad Rakhne Ke Liye)

| Cheez               | Purana Tareeka              | Modern Tareeka (Best)              | Kyon Better?                     |
|---------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| String banana       | ' ' ya " "                  | ` ` (backticks)                    | Multi-line + variables easy      |
| Variable jodna      | "Hello " + name             | `Hello ${name}`                    | Clean, no + signs                |
| Multi-line text     | "Line1\nLine2"              | `Line1<br>Line2`                   | Asaan aur readable               |
| Expression daalna   | "Sum: " + (2+3)             | `Sum: ${2+3}`                      | Direct calculation               |

